            "notes": "The main focus of this Elminster control deck is to disrupt the opponent's game plan through counterspells, removal, and card advantage while slowly building up card advantage and resources to eventually win the game. The deck includes a variety of counterspells like Counterspell, Force of Negation, and Mana Leak to prevent the opponent from resolving key threats. Removal spells like Swords to Plowshares and Wrath of God help deal with problematic creatures on the board. Card advantage is gained through spells like Fact or Fiction and Mystic Confluence. The deck also features powerful planeswalkers like Teferi, Hero of Dominaria and Teferi, Time Raveler to further control the game. Overall, the key strategy is to control the game, disrupt the opponent, and grind out a win through incremental advantage."
